25. dictator: an extraordinary magistrate appointed in time of peril. He held his office for six months only, and was preceded by twenty-four lictors with the fasces and axes. He had associated with him a lieutenant called the Master of Horse (nmgz'ster equitum), whom he usually appointed himself. As he had no colleague‚ and was irresponsible‚ his power was greater than that of the consul. impetum mora fregit: i.e. he checked HannibaPs victorious career by a policy of delay. His design was to harass Hannibal and tire him out, without risking a decisive battle. From the successful outcome of these tactics ‘ Fabian policy' has become proverbial.
